Kim Jong Il's Birthday Celebrated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- A meeting took place in Katmandu, Nepal, round table talks and a film show were held by the People's Unity Party of Tunisia and there was a seminar on the Songun idea in Kinshasa, Democratic Congo on Jan. 24 and 25 on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il.
 The participants of the film show watched the Korean film "Korean People's Army, Steel-Strong Ranks." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the Central Committee of the People's Front of Nepal Amik Sherchan who is deputy prime minister and minister of Health and Population in his speech at the meeting said that the people of the DPRK have achieved great successes in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, while meeting the challenges of the imperialists under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. The Nepalese people are extending unequivocal support and solidarity to the Korean people standing for independence, justice and democracy in their just cause of struggling against imperialism, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hussein Hamabi, member of the Political Bureau of the People's Unity of Tunisia who is deputy secretary general in charge of foreign relations of the party, said at the round-table talks that its party members are well aware of the great exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and extending firm solidarity to the Korean people in their resolute struggle against the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the Group for the Study of the Juche Idea at University of Kinshasa Bele Moukeleng addressing the seminar profoundly explained and proved the essence and position of the Songun idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting held in Nepal.

Symposium on Architectural Beauty Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- A symposium on the architectural beauty applied to the renovated East Pyongyang Grand Theatre was held at the theatre on Feb. 1.
 Speakers said that the theatre has been completely renovated as a centre of art in the Songun era as Kim Jong Il set forth the policy of making the structure formative and artistic and gave meticulous guidance to the project. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They explained that sculptural decorations were made to harmoniously match the whole appearance of the theatre and its three-dimensional space and pictorial style was creatively applied to decorating the theatre in order to make it appear formative and artistic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Decorations in the lobby and the inside of the theatre and its rest rooms include the large picture "Ullim Falls in Autumn" and various other sculptures, metal and wooden decorative works and so on which help the theatre appear elegant and fashionable in all its shapes to befit a modern art theatre, they noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Architectural creators succeeded in finding unique and peculiar methods to decorate all the structural edges, architectural elements and details and admirably applied the method of keeping architectural harmony from a formative and artistic point of view, thereby ensuring diversity in architectural space and style, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They emphasized that the overall renovation of the theatre helped the builders deepen their conviction that they can make any building formative and artistic on a high level when they, firmly armed with the Juche-based idea of architectural beauty propounded by the Workers' Party of Korea, enhance the level of their technical skills and rely on indigenous technology, raw materials and wisdom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the symposium were officials concerned, architects, creators, teachers, researchers and builders.

Implementation of June 15 Joint Declaration Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification reportedly issued a statement on Jan. 29 expressing the will of the youth and students to turn out in the struggle to implement the June 15 joint declaration by attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity.
 The statement recalled that the joint statement of the political parties, government and organizations of the DPRK set this year as a "year of attaching importance to the nation, maintaining peace and achieving unity" and called for widening the road for exchange of visits between the north and the south of Korea and the field of assemblies for reunification and continuing to develop June 15 All-Korean Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now that the United States and the pro-American conservative forces are becoming evermore pronounced in their moves against the reunification, the nation and the June 15 joint declaration, the slogan "Add brilliance to the June 15 reunification era by attaching importance to the nation, maintaining peace and achieving unity!" is hardening the will of all the Koreans for reunification, it said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The existence of the nation only can guarantee the future of its individual members, it said, adding that it is possible to defend peace and realize unity on the Korean Peninsula and shape the destiny of the nation only when the banner of attaching importance and top priority to the nation and defending it is upheld.

Fascist Tyrants Assailed for Fabricating Case to Kill Innocent People 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- Injustice and lies are bound to be brought to light to face a severe judgment.
 This is proved once again by the fact that those related to the "case of the People's Revolutionary Party," a typical fabricated "pro-communist case" during the period of "Yusin" dictatorship, were declared not guilty in south Korea some time ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said court ruling means a victory of the south Korean people who have dynamically struggled in recent years in demand of the probe into truth behind various cases fabricated during the period of the fascist dictatorial regime and a stern punishment to the traitors who mercilessly suppressed and killed innocent people to maintain it and their descendants. Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "case of the People's Revolutionary Party" is just a tip of iceberg of numerous treacherous and inhumane false cases and killings committed by the fascist dictators of south Korea in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Looking back on the history of south Korea, the era of fascist dictatorial regimes that lasted several decades was characterized by the most shameful and barbarous and dark rule in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This being a hard reality, the Grand National Party of south Korea has refused neither to admit the crimes nor apologize for them, despite the facts that truth about the case faked up by its predecessors and their killings was probed and those who fell victim to it were declared not guilty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "presidential elections" are slated to take place in south Korea this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All candidates from the GNP are without exception the descendants of the fascist dictators. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as a pikestaff that if they are allowed to come to power it is impossible to prevent the fabrication of more cases similar to the above-mentioned case and the south Korean people are bound to fall victim to fascist dictatorship again though they strongly desire justice and progress.

New Stamp Issued in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- A stamp reflecting the idea of the joint New Year editorial has been issued in the DPRK.
 Printed in the stamp are the militant slogan "Let us usher in a great heyday of Songun Korea full of confidence in victory!" to be upheld by the Korean people this year and words "A year of great changes".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also figuring in it are a picture showing the time-honored native home of President Kim Il Sung in Mangyongdae to the meaning that the year will significantly commemorate his 95th birth anniversary and pictures showing the tasks set forth by the editorial to effect innovations in the sectors of agriculture and light industry and the four pilots of the national economy -- power, coal-mining and metal industries and rail transport. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The face-value of the stamp is 3 won.

New Method Estimating Cold Resistance of Trees Developed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- The Branch Academy of Forestry under the State Academy of Sciences has established a new method of accurately estimating cold resistance of trees.
 According to Director Kim Yong, various kinds of trees to be estimated are planted in the same experimental plot to observe for 7-9 months. And then the measured values are analyzed in the mathematical modeling way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It makes it possible to accurately estimate such cold resistance of the given trees as the minimum growth temperature and distributional height. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the estimation method by electric resistance needs less manpower and a short period. It can be applicable to all species of trees. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As one can measure the cold resistance of trees without wintering, the method is of great practical significance and attracts academic interest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The economic effectiveness of the method has been proved through long trial application. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wide introduction of the method has made a great progress in scientific research into forest and forestation including selecting proper ecological zones for valuable trees and acclimatization of plants.

All Koreans Called upon to Uphold Songun Policy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- The joint New Year editorial for this year advanced before the Koreans the tasks of giving importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity to glorify the June 15 era of reunification and underscored the need to firmly uphold the Songun policy, a powerful treasured sword for protecting the Korean nation.
 It is a due obligation and sacred duty for all the Koreans in the north, the south and overseas who live in the exciting June 15 era of reunification to uphold the Songun policy. Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Songun policy serves as a powerful weapon for defending the nation as it is displaying its great vitality in the struggle to carve out the destiny of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The past, present and future of the Korean nation would be unthinkable without the Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun policy means a treasured sword of justice for achieving the sovereignty of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Defending the national sovereignty is an issue related to the life and soul of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the mission and purpose of the Songun policy to achieve the sovereignty and creditably guarantee the peace and reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Without the Songun policy, the Koreans' efforts to achieve the reunification of the country and the sovereignty of the nation would have been proved to be a daydream in face of the U.S. imperialists' persistent moves to dominate the whole of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun policy is a patriotic treasured sword which reliably guarantees the peace on the Korean Peninsula and the security of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the reunification of Korea and the sovereignty of the nation are to be achieved, it is necessary to have the peace on the Korean Peninsula and the security of the nation guaranteed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though the U.S. imperialists are now hurling mud at the DPRK over its powerful war deterrent built up thanks to the Songun policy, the south Korean people are benefiting from it, much less suffering from it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun policy is not targeted against fellow countrymen but against the war-like forces at home and abroad disturbing the peace on the peninsula and doing harm to the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 How to approach the Songun policy is, therefore, is an important touchstone to tell patriotism from treachery.

Japanese Authorities Urged to Stop Suppression of Chongryon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- M. M. Alhassan, chairman of the Nigerian National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, on Jan. 19 sent a letter to the Japanese embassy in his country to protest against the Japanese authorities' campaign against the DPRK and the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon).
 The position of the DPRK is rising in international arena as the days go by and the Songun politics pursued by leader Kim Jong Il has served as a powerful weapon protecting the DPRK's sovereignty and peace and security of Northeast Asia and guaranteeing victorious advance of the cause of independence, the letter noted, and said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displeased with it, the United States and its henchmen are making every possible effort to stifle the DPRK and what is more serious is that the island country is acting rashly against the DPRK and the Korean residents in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We, who value justice and peace, vehemently denounce the unjust deeds of the reactionaries of Japan and urge its authorities to immediately stop all sorts of moves against the DPRK and Chongryon and apologize to the Korean people and the world progressives for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is the only way out for Japan to improve its muddy image, the letter stressed.
